Aaron Plaxton
Investment Advisor







Aaron Plaxton
Investment Advisor

Having joined the Haywood team in 2005, Aaron is a licensed Investment Advisor (BC, AB, SK, ON, NS, YK) and holds the Canadian Investment Management (CIM) designation.
Aaron's focus is on developing long-term, mutually beneficial relationships with his clients. Ownership of individual equities and fixed income securities is the cornerstone of the Portfolio construction. Aaron brings a wealth of experience in retirement and investment planning, enabling him to develop portfolios that incorporate the appropriate investment classes. Commodity producing / exploration companies, Blue Chip companies, as well as international securities, form a significant portion of his investments.
Contact Aaron: (604) 697-6042 | Visit Aaron's Website
close








Alan Lane
Vice President, Investment Advisor







Alan Lane
Vice President, Investment Advisor

Alan has 30 years of experience in financial analysis and capital markets. He spent 15 years with BMO and CIBC in corporate banking, derivative structuring and sales and institutional equity sales. He then headed the institutional sales group at Dlouhy Merchant, a private brokerage firm later bought by Cantor Fitzgerald. For the last 11 years Alan has been a Vice President at Haywood in institutional equity sales covering a mixture of hedge funds, financial institutions and investment firms. Alan’s focus is on preserving and building capital. He is a graduate of McMaster University and has a MBA and CPA.
Contact Alan: (416) 507-2730
close








Alan Manzie
Vice President, Investment Advisor







Alan Manzie
Vice President, Investment Advisor

Alan began in his career in the business in 1986. He became a Branch Manager in 1990, a Divisional Manager in 1994 and received his Portfolio Managers license at the same time. In 1999 he transferred to the Private Bank at BMO as Director of Investments and joined Haywood shorty after. Alan designs income and growth portfolios and prefers to work on a discretionary basis. Alan was educated at the University of Sydney and the University of Alberta.
Contact Alan: (604) 697-7142 | Assistant: Kevin Guichon (604) 697-6056
close








Allan Frame
Vice President, Investment Advisor







Allan Frame
Vice President, Investment Advisor

Allan Frame joined Haywood in October 2015.  Al began his career as an Investment Advisor in Calgary in 1975.  Over the past 41 years he has held various titles and positions with several brokerage firms.  Al and his team specialize in raising capital, both public and private, for junior resource companies.  He is fully licensed in Canada and the United States.  
Prior to joining Haywood Al was with Richardson GMP and its predecessor firms going back to Yorkton Securities.  
 Contact: Allan (403) 509-1805 | Assistant: Gayle Elliott (403) 509-1923
close








Andrew Thomson
Vice President, Investment Advisor







Andrew Thomson
Vice President, Investment Advisor

Andrew joined Haywood in 2016 from Raymond James Ltd.  where he had worked for four years.   Prior, Andrew was a Branch Manager, VP and Investment Advisor at Canaccord Genuity.  He began his career in 1996  as a Financial Advisor at Scotia McLeod.  Over the past plus 20 years, Andrew has developed many long-term client relationship built on trust and exceptional customer service. 

Andrew has a Bachelor of Science in Economics from the University of Calgary and numerous securities industry accreditations.

Contact Andrew: (604) 697-6041  
close








Andrew Williams
Investment Advisor







Andrew Williams
Investment Advisor

Andrew came to Canada in September 2000 after completing his undergraduate degree in the UK. He initially took a role in the mining investment banking team with Endeavour Financial before joining Haywood in 2004. 
Andrew has over a decade of experience in the financial industry and his primary focus is on small to mid-cap companies within the natural resource sector.  Together with his partner, David Elliott they have made a significant contribution to many public and private mineral exploration companies, providing seed capital and subsequent financing for exploration and development.  Andrew and David not only supply capital to resource companies but are also actively involved with overseeing management of the companies to help them grow and achieve their full potential. 
He invests alongside his clients and specializes in investment strategies for high net worth individuals and international investment funds.
Contact Andrew: (604) 697-7443
close








Barry Muir
Investment Advisor







Barry Muir
Investment Advisor

Barry has been a Financial Advisor since 1998. Currently his main focus is on the derivatives market; option strategies for the bullish, bearish or neutral investor as a hedge or investment. In the mid-90s Barry worked his way up the ranks to Vice President of a junior mining company who had success in selling their Honduran gold exploration property to a senior gold producer. That experience led to working alongside The Long Wave Analyst, Ian Gordon, for 9 years, and helping to raise millions for various resource exploration companies. Barry is also a contributing author to Resource World Magazine.
Contact Barry: (604) 697-6172
close








