Advertisement


ShareOverview

Haywood Securities is in the business of buying and selling securities such as stocks, bonds, mutual funds and other investment-related products. This broker is registered with the SEC (#49696) and can engage in securities transactions on behalf of its customers (as a broker) or for its own account (as a dealer). Registered with 46 U.S. states and territoriesMission Statement: "We continually strive to enhance our practice of providing clients with ideas and investments that are well-founded and profitable."
Firm data current as of 12/31/2015




States RegisteredMap above shows the states and territories in which the Haywood Securities is registered for business.

 





Advertisement


ShareTypes of BusinessBroker Activities
In order to register with the SEC, all broker dealers must file Form BD through FINRA. In the last submission of SEC Form BD, Haywood Securities indicated that it operates in the following lines of business:




Securities Sales
Corporate Debt Securities and Over-The-Counter Corporate Equity Securities


Other Activities






Underwriting & Syndication
Exchange Member Transactions, Private Placements, and Corporate Securities Underwriter


Market Making
Put and Call Options

 





